{
  "texts": [
    "This improvement reduces the size and volume of micro-pores within the concrete matrix, leading to increased durability.",
    "The fine particle size of RHA helps fill voids and strengthens the cohesion between cementitious components.",
    "Additionally, Sakr et al. [64] found that RHA boosts the formation of calcium silicate hydrate (C-S-H) gel, a key hydration product that enhances the strength and durability of concrete.",
    "The increased C-S-H gel formation decreases porosity, resulting in a more compact and less permeable microstructure.",
    "This enhanced microstructural density minimizes pathways for water and aggressive ions, thereby improving the concrete resistance to degradation over time."
  ]
}